3.Job description

TalentNeuron is the world's leading provider of labor market analytics, delivering high-fidelity talent data on an unmatched global scale. TalentNeuron delivers actionable talent insight for every region of the world covering countries that collectively represent more than 90% of the world's GDP.


Through deep investments in machine learning and artificial intelligence, our technology platform ingests and normalizes hundreds of millions of structured and unstructured data points each day, delivering critical talent insights in support of workforce planning, strategic skills analysis, location optimization, DEI tactics, and sourcing strategies for local, regional, and global talent. These insights can be delivered to clients via software as a service, data as a service, or fully custom research efforts from our team of expert data scientists and advisors.


Our Core Values

Humanity First: We lead with humanity. We foster empathy, kindness, respect, and inclusiveness in all contexts and support one another.

Customers at the Core: We engage in meaningful and constant dialogue with clients to deeply understand and anticipate their needs, and consistently deliver exceptional value. We operate with integrity and do whats right for our clients, no matter how difficult.

Diverse Minds, One Team: We are curious and seek different perspectives and find common ground, but we act, succeed, fail, and celebrate as one. We openly collaborate, communicate, debate, and compromise across groups.

Pioneering Innovation: We take risks, fail fast, and learn from our experiments. We champion change and evolution without fear and inspire a culture where innovation thrives.

Resilient Perseverance: We think creatively and pragmatically to find solutions, remove barriers, and overcome obstacles. We are equally accountable for the results of the whole team and for our individual commitments, and we find a way to get things done by embracing a yes we can” attitude.


We are seeking a Business Analyst to join our Product Management team. This role is responsible for bridging the gap between customer needs, business objectives, and engineering execution. You will partner closely with Product Managers, Designers, and Engineers to translate high-level requirements and customer insights into detailed functional and technical specifications that guide successful product delivery.


Key Responsibilities

Collaborate with Product Managers to understand product vision, strategy, and customer needs.
Translate business objectives, user stories, and customer feedback into clear, actionable technical requirements for engineering teams.
Create and maintain requirement documentation, including process flows, acceptance criteria, data models, and system interaction diagrams.
Facilitate workshops and requirement-gathering sessions with stakeholders to validate assumptions and clarify scope.
Act as the subject matter expert during development cycles to ensure alignment between business goals and technical implementation.
Partner with QA and engineering teams to ensure requirements are testable, measurable, and traceable throughout the development lifecycle.
Support backlog refinement, prioritization, and sprint planning by clarifying requirements and dependencies.
Monitor product performance post-launch, gathering feedback to continuously refine requirements and identify improvement opportunities.

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in Business, Computer Science, Information Systems, or related field (or equivalent experience).
1 – 3 years of experience as a Business Analyst, Product Analyst, or similar role within a product-driven organization.
Previous experience or education in programming, preferably with Python, Javascript or Go.
Strong ability to break down abstract ideas into structured, detailed, and testable requirements.
Proficiency with tools such as Jira, Confluence, Miro, or equivalent.
Familiarity with Agile/Scrum methodologies and SDLC best practices.
Excellent communication and facilitation skills, with the ability to work across technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail.

Preferred Skills

Experience working directly with product management teams in a SaaS or technology environment.
Knowledge of APIs, data integrations, and system architecture concepts.
Comfort with SQL or data querying tools to validate requirements and test solutions.
Understanding of Data Warehouse/Data Lakehouse technologies.
Knowledge of Data Pipelines (Batch/Streaming processes)
Understanding HR technology systems or practices.

If you’re a Business Analyst ready to take on a challenging yet rewarding role, we encourage you to apply. At TalentNeuron, you’ll have the opportunity to analyze complex data, uncover actionable insights, and influence strategic decisions. We value analytical thinkers who thrive in collaborative environments and are passionate about driving business outcomes. Join us, leverage your expertise to exceed expectations, and be a key contributor to our success story. Apply now and help shape the future of TalentNeuron with data-driven innovation.

Role: Business Analyst
Industry Type: Analytics / KPO / Research
Department: Data Science & Analytics
Employment Type: Full Time, Permanent
Role Category: Business Intelligence & Analytics
Education
UG: B.Tech/B.E. in Any Specialization
