Identify project risks and suggest mitigation strategies.
Ensure changes to requirements are tracked, maintained, and implemented according to defined change management procedures.
Align requirements and designs, maintaining traceability from bank policies to epics, stories, and tasks.
Define effectiveness measures of the solution, analyze production issues, and provide solution proposals.
Contribute to the creation of training material and guides, while also supporting the wider Business Analysis community through training and peer reviews.
Demonstrate creative thinking by generating new ideas and concepts and identifying improved ways of doing things.
Utilize strong problem-solving skills for root cause analysis and quickly absorb and learn new systems, methodologies, and information.
Facilitate workshops, discussions, and meetings with stakeholders at all levels, showing leadership and driving change within the organization by building consensus and motivating others.
Form strong working relationships with stakeholders and team members, capable of working independently to resolve issues or identify solutions.
Possess strong negotiation and influencing skills, managing negotiations to achieve acceptable agreements between parties.
Proficient in tools such as Microsoft Office, Confluence, JIRA, Mural, and knowledge of key technologies like Cloud, AI/ML, API, Python, SQL is an added advantage.
