8. Job description
Key Responsibilities:

Lead and manage business analysis initiatives specific to iron ore mining operations, with a focus on enhancing operational efficiencies and maximizing resource utilization.
Drive Drill and Blast Design & Optimization efforts to improve blasting efficiency, minimize environmental impact, and enhance ore recovery.
Oversee Resource & Reserve Optimization activities ensuring accurate estimation, modeling, and forecasting to support sustainable mining operations.
Monitor and control Mining Critical Fleet through data-driven insights, ensuring optimal utilization, maintenance scheduling, and operational readiness.
Develop, track, and report on Mining KPIs, providing actionable insights to senior management for continuous performance improvement.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams including geology, mine planning, operations, and maintenance to align business objectives with mining processes.
Utilize advanced data analytics tools to interpret complex mining data, identify trends, and recommend process improvements.
Lead the implementation of best practices and innovative solutions to improve mining workflows and reduce operational costs.
Prepare detailed reports, dashboards, and presentations for stakeholders, highlighting key findings and strategic recommendations.
Mentor and guide junior business analysts and mining professionals in analytical methodologies and domain knowledge.

Preferred candidate profile

Expertise in Drill and Blast design and optimization techniques.
Proficient in mining software and fleet management tools (e.g., blast design software, telematics systems).
Advanced proficiency in data analytics tools such as Power BI, Tableau, SQL, Python/R.
Experience in KPI development, monitoring, and mining operations reporting.
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills.
Leadership experience with team and project management capabilities.
Ability to work collaboratively with cross-disciplinary teams.
The candidate must be willing to undertake extensive travel to site locations worldwide.
Excellent communication, reporting, and stakeholder management skills.
