10. Job description

Role & responsibilities


1. Market Analysis & Opportunity Assessment

Conduct market sizing studies for anode material, battery pack, BESS and renewable energy segments in India
Track competitive landscape: domestic and international
Analyze emerging demand signals from key customer cohorts: cell manufacturers , EV OEMs, utility operators, and C&I customers
Assess regulatory trends, policy support (PLI schemes, FAME, ACC incentives, ALMM/ALCM), and government renewable energy targets impacting addressable market
Evaluate market share potential at planned capacity scales
2. Financial Modeling & Valuation

Develop and maintain comprehensive financial models (DCF, sum-of-parts valuation) for platform businesses and individual projects
Support SPV-level financial analysis for discrete BESS and solar IPP projects, including IRR/ROCE calculations and equity return analysis
3. Equity Research & Competitor Analysis

Conduct comprehensive equity research on domestic and global competitors across the platform's value chain
Analyze publicly available equity research reports from leading Indian brokerages and global investment banks
Track quarterly results, management commentaries, and investor calls of listed peers to extract insights on capacity utilization trends, margin profiles, capex execution, and customer offtake patterns
Build comparative financial frameworks benchmarking Bhilwara Greentech's projected metrics against industry leaders
4. Industry Trends & Forward-Looking Analysis

Monitor and synthesize industry trend reports from the Industry
Track key industry developments: PLI scheme disbursements, ACC battery material incentives, FAME-III policy evolution, ALMM/ALCM compliance impacts, and grid code amendments for BESS integration
Analyze global supply chain shifts and their implications for needle coke pricing, synthetic graphite premiums, and domestic cell manufacturing cost curves
Develop proprietary industry dashboards consolidating trend data
4. Technical Due Diligence & Project Evaluation

5. Strategic Analytics

Analyze partnership opportunities: strategic JVs, technology licensing, supply chain collaboration
Evaluate inorganic growth opportunities (M&A, stake acquisitions, asset consolidation) aligned with platform strategy
Support tender analysis and competitive bidding for BESS and IPP (utility and C&I) contracts
6. Operational Performance Tracking

Support monthly/quarterly business reviews with data-driven insights and corrective action recommendations


Preferred candidate profile



Bachelors degree in Chemical Engineering (mandatory core requirement)
MBA from a reputed institution

Professional Experience

2-5 years of post-MBA experience in one or more of the following domains:
Battery/energy storage technology, Li-ion cell/pack manufacturing, or BMS/EMS systems

Renewable energy development, project finance, or utility-scale solar/wind/hydro

– Clean energy infrastructure, energy transition, or climate tech

– Strategy consulting with focus on energy, materials or manufacturing

– Corporate finance, M&A or investment banking in the infrastructure or industrial sector

